wfMcT1ModTable.name: wfMcT1ModTable
wfMcT1ModTable.description: MCT1 MOD record - Contains MCT1 module Configuration parameters

wfMcT1ModEntry.name: wfMcT1ModEntry
wfMcT1ModEntry.description: An entry in the MCT1 Base table

wfMcT1ModSlot.name: wfMcT1ModSlot
wfMcT1ModSlot.description: Instance ID slot, filled in by driver

wfMcT1ModPrimaryClock.name: wfMcT1ModPrimaryClock
wfMcT1ModPrimaryClock.description: Specifies the primary source for T1 transmit timing. Both T1 ports use the same T1 transmit timing source. The options for T1 timing source are internal timing source, loop timing from either T1 port and an external timing source.

wfMcT1ModSecondaryClock.name: wfMcT1ModSecondaryClock
wfMcT1ModSecondaryClock.description: Specifies the secondary source for T1 transmit timing. During normal operation T1 transmit timing is derived from the primary timing source. If the primary timing source fails, the software switches to secondary timing source.

wfMcT1ModCurrentClock.name: wfMcT1ModCurrentClock
wfMcT1ModCurrentClock.description: Indicates the clock source currently in use

wfMcT1ModExtClockOperational.name: wfMcT1ModExtClockOperational
wfMcT1ModExtClockOperational.description: Indicates whether the External clock is operational

wfMcT1ModLoop0ClockOperational.name: wfMcT1ModLoop0ClockOperational
wfMcT1ModLoop0ClockOperational.description: Indicates whether the timing source from port 1 is operational

wfMcT1ModLoop1ClockOperational.name: wfMcT1ModLoop1ClockOperational
wfMcT1ModLoop1ClockOperational.description: Indicates whether the timing source from port 2 is operational

wfMcT1ModRestart.name: wfMcT1ModRestart
wfMcT1ModRestart.description: Indicates Module gate should be restarted to read new configuration

wfMcT1Table.name: wfMcT1Table
wfMcT1Table.description: MCT1 line record - Contains MUNICH32 Configuration parameters

wfMcT1Entry.name: wfMcT1Entry
wfMcT1Entry.description: An entry in the MCT1 table

wfMcT1Slot.name: wfMcT1Slot
wfMcT1Slot.description: Instance ID Slot, filled in by driver

wfMcT1Connector.name: wfMcT1Connector
wfMcT1Connector.description: Instance ID Connector, filled in by driver

wfMcT1OperationMode.name: wfMcT1OperationMode
wfMcT1OperationMode.description: An option to generate and analyze specific test patterns is provided in BERT mode of operation. Only one T1 port can be in BERT mode at a time. This attribute selects normal or BERT mode of operation

wfMcT1Mtu.name: wfMcT1Mtu
wfMcT1Mtu.description: MTU parameter. Specifies the largest frame size that can be received by the MCT1 link module. Any received frame which is larger than the MTU will be discarded.

wfMcT1MunichVersion.name: wfMcT1MunichVersion
wfMcT1MunichVersion.description: Specifies version number of the MUNICH chip used

wfMcT1Dsx1LineType.name: wfMcT1Dsx1LineType
wfMcT1Dsx1LineType.description: Selects between the two framing formats supported - D4 and ESF. The sailent differences between the two formats are the number of frames per superframe and the use of F-bit position.

wfMcT1Dsx1ZeroCoding.name: wfMcT1Dsx1ZeroCoding
wfMcT1Dsx1ZeroCoding.description: Selects between the two Zero Code Suppression formats used on the link. In B8ZS coding, any outgoing stream of eight consecutive zeroes is replaced with a B8ZS code word. Any received B8ZS code is replaced with all zeroes.

wfMcT1Dsx1LoopbackConfig.name: wfMcT1Dsx1LoopbackConfig
wfMcT1Dsx1LoopbackConfig.description: Indicates the loopback configuration of the T1 interface. The interface can be in the following loopback states: Payload loopback and Line loopback or no loopback. The loopbacks can be initiated by the manager of this device or by the far end. The loopbacks initiated by the far end are NETREQPAYLOADLOOP and NETREQLINELOOP.

wfMcT1Dsx1LineStatus.name: wfMcT1Dsx1LineStatus
wfMcT1Dsx1LineStatus.description: Indicates the line status of the T1 interface. It contains loopback state and alarm state information. The Dsx1LineStatus is a bit map therefore it can represent multiple loopback and alarm states simultaneously.

wfMcT1Dsx1SetupAlarmThreshold.name: wfMcT1Dsx1SetupAlarmThreshold
wfMcT1Dsx1SetupAlarmThreshold.description: Specifies setup time for performance failure conditions, in seconds. When a performance defect is present for greater than the time specified by this parameter a performance failure is registered and a message is logged.

wfMcT1Dsx1ClearAlarmThreshold.name: wfMcT1Dsx1ClearAlarmThreshold
wfMcT1Dsx1ClearAlarmThreshold.description: Specifies clear time for performance failure conditions, in seconds. When a performance failure condition has been cleared for greater than the time specified by this parameter then the failure cleared condition is registered and a message is logged.

wfMcT1Dsx1SignalLevel.name: wfMcT1Dsx1SignalLevel
wfMcT1Dsx1SignalLevel.description: Specifies T1 transmit power level, in terms of DB. They translate into cable length as follows: 0.0dB -> 0-133 ft 0.5dB -> 133-266 ft 0.8dB -> 266-399 ft 1.1dB -> 399-533 ft 1.5dB -> 533-655 ft

wfMcT1LoopbackDisable.name: wfMcT1LoopbackDisable
wfMcT1LoopbackDisable.description: The MCT1 link module is capable of detecting loop up and loop down codes received from the far end. This parameter enables or disbales loop up/down code detection circuitry

wfMcT1Dsx1FDLOperationMode.name: wfMcT1Dsx1FDLOperationMode
wfMcT1Dsx1FDLOperationMode.description: Select between the two FDL modes of operation. The AT&T mode, 54016 is based on AT&T publication 54015-1989. The ANSI mode, T1403 is based on ANSI publication T1.403-1989

wfMcT1BertTxOutputLevel.name: wfMcT1BertTxOutputLevel
wfMcT1BertTxOutputLevel.description: Specifies T1 transmit power level, in terms of DB while the T1 port is in BERT mode. The power levels translate into cable length as follows: 0.0dB -> 0-133 ft 0.5dB -> 133-266 ft 0.8dB -> 266-399 ft 1.1dB -> 399-533 ft 1.5dB -> 533-655 ft

wfMcT1BertTestMode.name: wfMcT1BertTestMode
wfMcT1BertTestMode.description: Selects between the framing formats while in bert mode of operation.

wfMcT1BertLineCode.name: wfMcT1BertLineCode
wfMcT1BertLineCode.description: Selects between the two Zero Code Suppression formats used on the link while in BERT mode. In B8ZS coding, any outgoing stream of eight consecutive zeroes is replaced with a B8ZS code word. Any received B8ZS code is replaced with all zeroes.

wfMcT1BertTestPattern.name: wfMcT1BertTestPattern
wfMcT1BertTestPattern.description: When a T1 port is in BERT mode, it is capable of generating a set of known patterns. This paramater selects between those patterns

wfMcT1BertSendAlarm.name: wfMcT1BertSendAlarm
wfMcT1BertSendAlarm.description: Specifies a blue or yellow alarm to be transmitted while in BERT mode.

wfMcT1DS2282Version.name: wfMcT1DS2282Version
wfMcT1DS2282Version.description: Specifies version number of DS2282 chip

wfMcT1Restart.name: wfMcT1Restart
wfMcT1Restart.description: Indicates Port gate should be restarted to read new configuration

wfMcT1Loopback.name: wfMcT1Loopback
wfMcT1Loopback.description: Selects line or payload loopback to be activated locally

wfMcT1FDLTargetAddress.name: wfMcT1FDLTargetAddress
wfMcT1FDLTargetAddress.description: Selects between the two FDL target address modes

wfMcT1ConfigTable.name: wfMcT1ConfigTable
wfMcT1ConfigTable.description: MCT1 configuration record - Contains MUNICH32 and Framer write only Configuration parameters

wfMcT1ConfigEntry.name: wfMcT1ConfigEntry
wfMcT1ConfigEntry.description: An entry in the MCT1 Config table

wfMcT1ConfigSlot.name: wfMcT1ConfigSlot
wfMcT1ConfigSlot.description: Instance ID Slot, filled in by driver

wfMcT1ConfigConnector.name: wfMcT1ConfigConnector
wfMcT1ConfigConnector.description: Instance ID Connector, filled in by driver

wfMcT1BertPayldLb.name: wfMcT1BertPayldLb
wfMcT1BertPayldLb.description: Selects a payload loopback code to be sent to the far end by the FDL while in BERT mode. It can be a payload loopback activate or deactivate code.

wfMcT1BertLineLb.name: wfMcT1BertLineLb
wfMcT1BertLineLb.description: Selects a line loopback code to be sent to the far end while in BERT mode. It can be a line loopback activate or deactivate code using the hardware on the MCT1 board or it can be a code sent by the FDL.

wfMcT1BertErrorInsert.name: wfMcT1BertErrorInsert
wfMcT1BertErrorInsert.description: Indicates that an error be injected into the transmitted data stream while in BERT mode.

wfMcT1Dsx1SendLoopCode.name: wfMcT1Dsx1SendLoopCode
wfMcT1Dsx1SendLoopCode.description: Selects a Loop Up/Down code to be sent to the remote end

wfMcT1Dsx1SendFDLCode.name: wfMcT1Dsx1SendFDLCode
wfMcT1Dsx1SendFDLCode.description: Selects an FDL code to be sent to the remote end

wfMcT1LineTable.name: wfMcT1LineTable
wfMcT1LineTable.description: MCT1 Channel record - Contains configuration parameters and statistics for MUNICH32 which are channel specific.

wfMcT1LineEntry.name: wfMcT1LineEntry
wfMcT1LineEntry.description: An entry in the MCT1CHANNEL table

wfMcT1LineSlot.name: wfMcT1LineSlot
wfMcT1LineSlot.description: Instance ID Slot, filled in by driver

wfMcT1LineConnector.name: wfMcT1LineConnector
wfMcT1LineConnector.description: Instance ID Connector, filled in by driver

wfMcT1LineLine.name: wfMcT1LineLine
wfMcT1LineLine.description: Line number for this line instance, filled in by driver. The line number corresponds to the position of the circuit, from 1 to 24, on the port.

wfMcT1LineCct.name: wfMcT1LineCct
wfMcT1LineCct.description: Circuit number for this line instance

wfMcT1LineBofl.name: wfMcT1LineBofl
wfMcT1LineBofl.description: Selects Breath of Life (BOFL) parameter. If selected, a BOFL packet is sent out on the wire as often as specifies by the wfMcT1LineBoflTmo parameter

wfMcT1LineBoflTmo.name: wfMcT1LineBoflTmo
wfMcT1LineBoflTmo.description: Indicates the time-period between BOFL packets

wfMcT1LineFractionalLpbk.name: wfMcT1LineFractionalLpbk
wfMcT1LineFractionalLpbk.description: Any circuit on this T1 port is capable of being put into loopback, i.e. data coming into that circuit from the wire is mirrorred back onto the wire. This parameter enables or disables this loopback feature on any circuit.

wfMcT1LineChannelAssignment.name: wfMcT1LineChannelAssignment
wfMcT1LineChannelAssignment.description: Lists the time-slots which constitute this channel. User types in a list of time-slots from 1 to 24 separated by commas

wfMcT1LineMadr.name: wfMcT1LineMadr
wfMcT1LineMadr.description: Line MAC address, fixed - line driver fills in from the 48 bit address stored in the serial number prom.

wfMcT1LineWanProtocol.name: wfMcT1LineWanProtocol
wfMcT1LineWanProtocol.description: WAN protocol selection is provided via this parameter. The supported protocols can be selected per circuit.

wfMcT1LineService.name: wfMcT1LineService
wfMcT1LineService.description: Service type for this circuit. Supports raw HDLC mode. Does not support LLC1 at this time. LLC1 mode will prefix the HDLC address and control fields to the frame. May support LLC1 mode in the future

wfMcT1LineRateAdaption.name: wfMcT1LineRateAdaption
wfMcT1LineRateAdaption.description: Determines the number of bits and their bit positions within the time-slot. 64k selection uses all 8 bits in the time-slot. The two 56k selections use 7 of the 8 bits in the time-slot. 56k_MSB does not use the most significant bit and 56k_LSB does not use the least significant bit in the time-slot.

wfMcT1LineIFTF.name: wfMcT1LineIFTF
wfMcT1LineIFTF.description: Determines the Interframe time fill character to be transmitted by the MUNICH. In case of IFTF_FLAGS, 0x7E is sent and in case of IFTF_IDLES 0xff is sent as the interframe timefill characters.

wfMcT1LineCRCSize.name: wfMcT1LineCRCSize
wfMcT1LineCRCSize.description: Determines the CRC Size. When CRC32 is selected a 32 bit CRC is appended to the frame being transmitted and a 32 bit CRC check is performed on the received frame. When CRC16 is selected, a 16 bit CRC is appended to the transmitted frame and a 16 bit CRC is performed. on the received frame.

wfMcT1LineRxOctets.name: wfMcT1LineRxOctets
wfMcT1LineRxOctets.description: Number of octets received without error

wfMcT1LineRxFrames.name: wfMcT1LineRxFrames
wfMcT1LineRxFrames.description: Number of frames received without error

wfMcT1LineTxOctets.name: wfMcT1LineTxOctets
wfMcT1LineTxOctets.description: Number of octets transmitted without error

wfMcT1LineTxFrames.name: wfMcT1LineTxFrames
wfMcT1LineTxFrames.description: Number of frames transmitted without error

wfMcT1LineLackRxResources.name: wfMcT1LineLackRxResources
wfMcT1LineLackRxResources.description: Number of Rx frames dropped due to lack of buffer resources

wfMcT1LineLackTxResources.name: wfMcT1LineLackTxResources
wfMcT1LineLackTxResources.description: Number of Tx frames dropped due to lack of buffer resources

wfMcT1LineTxUnderflows.name: wfMcT1LineTxUnderflows
wfMcT1LineTxUnderflows.description: Number of Tx frames dropped due to Transmit underflow

wfMcT1LineRxOverflows.name: wfMcT1LineRxOverflows
wfMcT1LineRxOverflows.description: Number of Rx frames dropped due to Receive overflow

wfMcT1LineRxNullFrames.name: wfMcT1LineRxNullFrames
wfMcT1LineRxNullFrames.description: Number of short frames received (with no data bytes)

wfMcT1LineRxShortFrames.name: wfMcT1LineRxShortFrames
wfMcT1LineRxShortFrames.description: Number of short frames received (less than or equal to two data bytes)

wfMcT1LineTurboBofl.name: wfMcT1LineTurboBofl
wfMcT1LineTurboBofl.description: DEBUG parameter - Turbo bofl enabled or disabled

wfMcT1LineBoflNum.name: wfMcT1LineBoflNum
wfMcT1LineBoflNum.description: DEBUG parameter - Number of breath of life packets per breath of life

wfMcT1LineBoflLen.name: wfMcT1LineBoflLen
wfMcT1LineBoflLen.description: DEBUG parameter - breath of life packet length

wfMcT1LineRxReplenMisses.name: wfMcT1LineRxReplenMisses
wfMcT1LineRxReplenMisses.description: Count of number of packet buffer misses while attempting to replenish driver receive ring

wfMcT1LineRxIFCs.name: wfMcT1LineRxIFCs
wfMcT1LineRxIFCs.description: Number of times the device changes its interframe time-fill

wfMcT1LineTxQueueEmpty.name: wfMcT1LineTxQueueEmpty
wfMcT1LineTxQueueEmpty.description: The number of times the transmit ring is found empty when transmitting packets

wfMcT1LineMtu.name: wfMcT1LineMtu
wfMcT1LineMtu.description: MTU read-only parameter. Specifies the largest frame size that can be received by the MCT1 link module. Any received frame which is larger than the MTU will be discarded. Can be set in MCT1Entry TABLE by the user

wfMcT1LineRestart.name: wfMcT1LineRestart
wfMcT1LineRestart.description: Indicates channel gate should be restarted to read new configuration

wfMcT1LineLineNumber.name: wfMcT1LineLineNumber
wfMcT1LineLineNumber.description: line number for this line instance

wfMcT1Dsx1CurrentEntry.description: per circuit MCT1_DSX1 current objects - wfMcT1Dsx1CurrentIndex corresponds to Wellfleet circuit number

wfMcT1Dsx1CurrentConnector.description: this corresponds to the Wellfleet Connector number

wfMcT1Dsx1IntervalConnector.name: wfMcT1Dsx1IntervalConnector
wfMcT1Dsx1IntervalConnector.description: this corresponds to the Wellfleet Connector number

wfMcT1Dsx1IntervalNumber.name: wfMcT1Dsx1IntervalNumber
wfMcT1Dsx1IntervalNumber.description: 1..96 where 1 is the most recent 15-minute interval and 96 is the least

wfMcT1Dsx1IntervalESs.name: wfMcT1Dsx1IntervalESs
wfMcT1Dsx1IntervalESs.description: the number of errored seconds in the specified interval

wfMcT1Dsx1IntervalSESs.name: wfMcT1Dsx1IntervalSESs

wfMcT1Dsx1IntervalBESs.name: wfMcT1Dsx1IntervalBESs

wfMcT1Dsx1TotalSESs.name: wfMcT1Dsx1TotalSESs

wfMcT1Dsx1TotalUASs.name: wfMcT1Dsx1TotalUASs

wfMcT1Dsx1TotalCSSs.name: wfMcT1Dsx1TotalCSSs
